HEADWORD: Blastoidea
<hw>Blas*toid"e*a</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
fr. Gr. <grk>blasto`s</grk> sprout + <ets>-oid</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>One of the divisions of Crinoidea found fossil
in paleozoic rocks; pentremites. They are so named on account of their
budlike form.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Blastomere</ent>⟦br⟧
